  'shelf-installation-salisbury': {
    metaDescription:
      'Shelf installation in Salisbury — floating shelves, alcove shelving, garage racking, secure fixing to solid stone, brick, and plasterboard walls. Fully insured. FixWell Services.',

    intro:
      'Getting shelves to hang level, secure, and in exactly the right position requires the right fixing for the specific wall type — and Salisbury homes present an unusually wide range, from Victorian solid limestone walls in the Cathedral Close to modern dot-and-dab plasterboard partitions in 2010s new-builds. FixWell Services installs shelves and shelving systems across Salisbury and Wiltshire, using the correct fixing specification for each wall type. Call +44 7391 599 078 or use the quote form.',

    sections: [
      {
        heading: 'What Shelf Installation Involves',
        body: 'Shelf installation is more than drilling holes and inserting plugs. The process begins with understanding what the shelf will carry (books weigh approximately 15–20kg per linear metre; a loaded kitchen shelf with crockery can exceed 30kg), which determines the bracket type, spacing, and fixing specification. Wall type is the second critical variable: solid limestone and flint walls in central Salisbury require SDS hammer drill bits and frame plugs rated for masonry; timber stud walls with plasterboard require the screw to reach the timber stud directly for load-bearing applications; hollow plasterboard cavities (dot-and-dab off a masonry backing wall) require specialist hollow-wall anchors that expand behind the plasterboard skin. Identifying the wall construction before drilling — using a combination of sounding (knock test), magnetic stud finder, and pipe/cable detector — prevents both structural damage and the embarrassment of a shelf pulling off the wall under load.',
      },
      {
        heading: 'Wall Types in Salisbury Homes and the Correct Fixing',
        body: 'Salisbury\'s housing stock presents a representative cross-section of English building history. Properties in and around the Cathedral Close, Crane Street, and The Close itself are often built in Chilmark limestone or Purbeck stone — solid walls of 300–600mm thickness that provide excellent fixing strength provided the right masonry plug and drill bit are used. Victorian terraces throughout Fisherton Street, St Marks, and Milne Close have solid brick construction. 1960s–80s properties on the Bemerton Heath and Harnham estates predominantly use cavity wall construction with an inner leaf of thermalite or breeze block and a plasterboard internal finish. Modern properties (2000s+) commonly use timber stud or metal stud internal partitions with plasterboard on both faces — here a multi-scanner is essential to locate the studs before drilling. Dot-and-dab walls (plasterboard bonded to masonry with adhesive dabs) have a cavity behind the plasterboard that prevents standard plugs from gripping — Gripit or spring toggle anchors are used in this configuration.',
      },
      {
        heading: 'How FixWell Installs Shelves',
        body: 'We begin every shelf installation job by scanning the wall with a combined stud-finder and pipe/cable detector — a step that protects both the customer\'s property and our team from the risk of drilling into hidden services. We establish a level reference line using a laser level for multi-shelf runs or a spirit level for single shelves. Brackets are positioned precisely against the reference line, pilot holes are drilled at the correct diameter and depth for the chosen fixing, plugs are seated fully in the hole, and brackets are fixed with screws torqued to the manufacturer specification. For floating shelves with concealed brackets, we ensure the drill depth matches the bracket rod length precisely to allow the shelf to seat flush against the wall. Weight testing after installation is standard — we apply a downward load to each bracket before handing over, confirming that every fixing is secure before we leave.',
      },
      {
        heading: 'Shelf Types, Load Capacity, and Cost in Salisbury',
        body: 'The most frequently requested shelf types in Salisbury homes are floating white-painted MDF shelves (IKEA LACK style, concealed bracket), solid timber shelves on visible L-brackets or decorative iron brackets for kitchen and living room use, and alcove shelves in chimney breast recesses. Alcove shelves are particularly popular in the many Victorian terraced properties in Salisbury where original chimney breasts survive — we make the shelves to the exact alcove width, using timber battens fixed to the side walls as the support rail, producing a neat built-in appearance. For garages, workshops, and loft spaces we install wire or timber racking systems on the same fixed-price basis. Our standard rate of £20–£40/hr makes a two-shelf living room installation a typically one-to-two-hour job. We provide the brackets and fixings; customers supply the shelves, or we can source and supply timber cut to size.',
      },
      {
        heading: 'Shelf Fitting as Part of Carpentry and Odd-Jobs Services',
        body: 'Shelf installation sits naturally within both FixWell\'s carpentry services and our odd-jobs service in Salisbury. On a typical odd-jobs visit, shelf fitting is often combined with picture and mirror hanging, curtain rail installation, and TV wall mounting — making a single two-to-three-hour booking a highly efficient way to address a list of small household tasks. For more involved shelving projects — alcove built-ins, full wall shelving runs, or utility room racking — we treat the job as a carpentry project and quote accordingly. If you are a landlord or letting agent wanting standard shelving fitted in a rental property to a consistent specification across multiple units, we can work to your brief and provide a per-property cost. Contact FixWell Services on +44 7391 599 078 or use the quote form to get started.',
      },
    ],

    faqs: [
      {
        q: 'Can you fix shelves to solid stone or brick walls in Salisbury?',
        a: 'Yes. Solid masonry walls — including the limestone and flint construction common in older Salisbury properties — provide excellent fixing strength when drilled with the correct SDS masonry bit and fitted with appropriately rated frame plugs or Rawlbolts for heavier loads.',
      },
      {
        q: 'How do you know where the studs are in a plasterboard wall?',
        a: 'We use a combined electronic stud finder and pipe/cable detector before drilling any wall. For stud walls we confirm stud location by drilling a small pilot hole at the stud position before the full fixing hole.',
      },
      {
        q: 'My walls are dot-and-dab plasterboard — can you still fix shelves?',
        a: 'Yes, but the fixing specification is different. Dot-and-dab walls have a cavity behind the plasterboard that standard plugs cannot grip. We use specialist hollow-wall anchors (Gripit, spring toggle, or Duopower) that expand behind the plasterboard skin to provide a secure hold.',
      },
      {
        q: 'Can you make alcove shelves to fit a Victorian chimney breast recess?',
        a: 'Yes. Alcove shelving in chimney breast recesses is one of our most popular Salisbury jobs. We fix timber battens to the side walls of the alcove and cut shelves to the exact width. We can paint or finish them to match your room, or leave them natural timber.',
      },
      {
        q: 'How heavy can the shelves be once installed?',
        a: 'Load capacity depends on the wall type and fixing specification. A standard bracket on solid masonry with a frame plug can support 50kg or more per bracket. On plasterboard with hollow-wall anchors, we limit loads to around 10–15kg per fixing point. We will advise the safe load limit for your specific installation.',
      },
      {
        q: 'Do you supply the shelves and brackets or do I need to provide them?',
        a: 'We supply all fixings (plugs, screws, brackets where specified). Customers typically provide the shelves, but if you need timber cut to size or standard brackets sourced, we can include these at cost with advance notice.',
      },
    ],
  },

